  "prompt": "What is the average weight of an Apple?",
  "response": "The average weight of a typical apple (the fruit) is approximately **182 grams** (about **6.4 ounces**). However, the weight can vary depending on the variety and size of the apple. Here's a general breakdown:\n\n- **Small apples:** Around 150 grams (5.3 ounces)\n- **Medium apples:** Approximately 182 grams (6.4 ounces)\n- **Large apples:** Up to 250 grams (8.8 ounces) or more\n\nDifferent apple varieties may also have slight differences in weight. For example:\n\n- **Gala apples:** Typically medium-sized, averaging around 150-200 grams\n- **Fuji apples:** Often larger, ranging from 200-250 grams\n- **Granny Smith apples:** Usually medium to large, averaging between 170-220 grams\n\nKeep in mind that these are average weights, and individual apples may be lighter or heavier based on growing conditions and specific cultivars.",
